               <p>EDWARD JONES. I am a <rs id="t18270405-239-viclabel1313" type="occupation">stationer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-239-victim1335 t18270405-239-viclabel1313"></join>, and live in Budgerow - the prisoner was my <rs id="t18270405-239-deflabel1314" type="occupation">warehouseman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-239-defend1334 t18270405-239-deflabel1314"></join> for about sixteen years. This paper is mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-239-person1336">
                  JOHN 
                  WILLIS
               <interp inst="t18270405-239-person1336" type="surname" value="WILLIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-239-person1336" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-239-person1336" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have bought paper of the prisoners at different times, within the last eighteen months; he sold me all this paper at different times; the last he sold me was this double-milled blue paper - I bought it on the 9th of February - he called for the money on the 10th; I knew him by the name of Wilson, but Mr. Candle was in my shop, and called him Ballard; when he was gone away Candle told me where he lived - he had told me he was a glazier, and took the paper for work. I informed Mr. Jones.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-239-person1337">
